"{\"uid\": \"trendydigests.com-2024-03-15-paris-mayor-stands-firm-on-eco-friendly-olympics-rejects-air-conditioning-for-2024-games\", \"text\": \"Published on  In a world grappling with climate change and extreme weather patterns, hosting an environmentally sustainable sporting event has become a paramount concern. The Paris Mayor, Anne Hidalgo, has taken a bold stand in preparation for the 2024 Olympics, advocating for a \\\"Green Games\\\" and, most notably, a no air conditioning stance in the athletes' village despite the expected heatwaves.  Hidalgo's position on air conditioning has been questioned due to the expected rise in temperatures during the upcoming European summer following the unprecedented heat in 2023. However, the athlete's village for Paris 2024 is set to be distinctive, featuring a cooling system that utilizes groundwater and structures positioned to reduce direct sunlight exposure. \\\"This village was designed to avoid the need for air conditioning, even in very, very high temperatures, in order to maintain comfortable temperatures,\\\" Hidalgo explained.  The Paris 2024 organizers have declared an ambitious goal to halve the carbon footprint compared to the Rio 2016 and London 2012 Summer Games. Hidalgo urged nations and athletes to \\\"trust the science,\\\" citing the dire warnings from climate scientists about our proximity to environmental catastrophe and the sober design of buildings that make air conditioning unnecessary.  This innovative approach has not been widely accepted. Some Olympic Committees, such as Australia, Brazil, Canada, and Norway, are still skeptical. Canada's Olympic Committee has revealed plans to introduce heat mitigation strategies in addition to Paris 2024, which includes using air conditioning units for severe heat conditions.  Australia and Brazil are also considering portable air conditioners for their athletes, with Brazil highlighting the \\\"heat forecast\\\" as a rationale for their investment in air conditioning units.\\\"Our clear wish is that there should be air-conditioning in all rooms,\\\" the Norwegian Committee told Reuters, with Brazil saying \\\"the heat forecast\\\" made it \\\"necessary to invest in renting air-conditioning units for the entire delegation\\\".  Despite these concerns, several other delegations have expressed their trust in the existing cooling system. The German Olympic Committee said after visits to the Olympic Village, \\\"We rate the clever cooling system installed in floor and ceiling to be sufficient for the climate zone,\\\" highlighting that the majority of their federations find additional air conditioning unnecessary.  The long-term vision for the athletes' village, which post-Games will become a neighborhood home to thousands of Parisians, has not been lost on Hidalgo. \\\"These new buildings will not need air conditioning, so we are working for the long term,\\\" she stated, underscoring the sustainability of the project beyond the immediacy of the Olympics.  The city's comprehensive environmental strategy reflects its preparations for the Olympics, including investments in cycle paths, green spaces, and building insulation.By 2050, Paris aims to reduce energy consumption by 30% and achieve carbon neutrality, with the first stage of success to be showcased during the 2024 Olympics.Hidalgo's stance, though controversial, is clear. She remains steadfast in her commitment to a sustainable future for Paris, even as she defies traditional expectations of comfort for the world's elite athletes.  Relevant articles:-'Trust science', Paris mayor tells air conditioning fans ahead of Olympics-'Trust science', Paris mayor tells fans of air conditioning, The Straits Times, Thu, 14 Mar 2024 07:54:00 GMT-What Are the Updates for Paris Olympics 2024 So Far? - Construction, Laws, Updates Revealed, EssentiallySports, Thu, 30 Nov 2023 08:00:00 GMT-Paris 2024: The untenable promise of 'climate positive' Games, Le Monde, Wed, 31 May 2023 07:00:00 GMT